snippet.textDisplay: I loved a girl a lot, I loved her so much that I loved her more than my own life, but she was not mine, only I know how sad I was, how much my heart ached, how many tears I shed sitting on the bank of the river. This song is my favorite, I find the words of my heart in this song, especially on a moonlight night, I listen to this song again and again. Finally, I will say 'Nyoon la liya be-parwaah de naal' I’ve given my heart to an uncaring beloved....

snippet.textDisplay: Last night, I fell asleep listening to music on Spotify.  I drifted off to sleep and into a vivid dream where someone played a very beautiful, magical song.  The experience was so intense, it felt like I was both asleep and awake at the same time.  At one point, I actually woke up, checked my phone to see what was playing, restarted the song, and then fell back asleep.  The next morning, I checked my recently played list and discovered the song was "Neun La Leya."  It was the same magical melody from my dream.  It's hard to put into words just how profound the experience was.

It's hard to put into words just how profound the experience was.

snippet.textDisplay:
the one thought i have to share after hearing this song for the hundredth time - it doesn't matter any longer whether i keep a count of it or not in any case, or whether i keep a record of the country of its origin, or the identity of the people who made it possible in the first place - is the following:

in case one is following one who doesn't know what it means to follow anyone else other than himself, 

then what dharma is that person following? 

can anyone suggest the best name for that dharma? 

which will be acceptable to everyone else? 

for all eternity? 

everyone here is welcome to try!

and therefore, noone is forced to believe that the name given by an other one is the best name among all the possible names that can exist for it. 

for all eternity by the way. 

so, try now. 

or else, 

give up trying. i have too.

and just enjoy the experience of listening to the song. 

while it lasts. 

to kaavish and to coke studio: thank you. 

thank you all.
